  <oversight_info>
    <has_dmc>No</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Recently, research studies have shown that patients who have had trouble taking statins every
      day, are able to take statins if they take them only once or twice a week. The investigators
      are doing a research study which involves switching people who are taking ezetimibe to the
      statin Crestor once or twice a week and to see how ell Crestor lowers cholesterol and if it
      is tolerated.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
